Online Cryptography Course Data Analysis

Defining the Analytic Question

Identify individuals most likely to click on her ads

Defining the metric of success

Mapping out individuals most likely to click on the ad using different visualization techniques and summary statistics,

Understanding the context

A Kenyan entrepreneur has started an online cryptography course online and would to identify individuals that are mostly likely to click on the ads based on the data she collected a while back before posting in her blog.

Recording the experimental design

  • Loading the dataset

  • Cleaning the data

  • Performing necessary exploratory data analysis

  • Making conclusions and recommendations based on the findings gotten.

Data Relevance

This dataset has relevant variables such as city, country, daily time spent, daily internet usage, time stamp etc which will aid in giving insights on the type of individual most likely to click on the ad.

From the correlation matrix we can deduce the following:

Variables that are positively correlated are:

  • Daily internet usage and age
  • Clicked on ad and Age
  • Daily time spent on the site and daily internet usage.

Variables that are negatively correlated are:

  • Clicked on ad and daily internet usage

  • Age and daily internet usage

  • Clicked on Ad and area income

  • Age and daily time spent on site

Conclusion

Based on the analysis:

  • When consumers spend more on internet usage doesnt necessary mean that they will click on the ad

  • When time spent on the ad is less than 30 they are more likely to click on the ad compared to those that spent a long time on the internet

  • The higher the area income the lower the chances an individual will click on the ad

Recommendation

I would recommend that the ads should target individuals whose area income range from 3000, has spent less than 40 units on the internet which could prompt the potential client to click on the ad, and less internet usage(less than 150). Intuitively, this makes sense as individuals that spend less time both on usage and time might have garnered interest probably if it was the first ad they came across or were briefly browsing the net and the ad suddenly popped up. Targeting older people (50 and above) as seen from the correlation matrix, are more likely to spend less time on the site.
